  "texts": [
    "Consider the scenario of a data owner, who wants to make their dataset publicly available but also wants to prevent untrusted entities like model owner A, from fine-tuning an arbitrary model M on the released data D train c ⊂ D c.",
    "With LLMs being increasingly trained on internet-scraped data, data owners must protect their data from such unsolicited use.",
    "To facilitate data sharing with untrusted parties (i.e., internet), consider a function T that transforms X c such that the transformed dataset",
    "ensures that while M converges on the transformed dataset, it fails to perform well on the unseen test setting, where the downstream test dataset D test c remains untouched, i.e., is clean.",
    "Further, we ensure that the semantic meaning and the labels of D train u remain the same."
  ],
